The Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Boss Mustapha, has expressed shock at the deplorable state of Nigeria’s healthcare system. Mustapha said he never knew Nigeria’s healthcare system was so bad until he was appointed to head the task force on COVID-19. Intensify prayers, covid-19 is a matter of life and death, Buhari urges Nigerians The SGF prayed that the COVID-19 spread Nigeria does not escalate, adding that the country lacked what is required to handle the situation. Mustapha also said the cash donations for the pandemic will not be handled by the task force, noting that transparency and accountability are important in fighting the pandemic.